The article is a statement by the President of the United States, announcing the intention to recognize Southern Sudan as a sovereign, independent state in July 2011. The President congratulates the people of Southern Sudan for a successful referendum where an overwhelming majority voted for independence. He emphasizes the need for all parties to ensure that this historic moment becomes a moment of lasting progress by fully implementing the Comprehensive Peace Agreement and resolving outstanding disputes peacefully. The President also pledges continued support to the aspirations of all Sudanese and promises to work with both Sudan and Southern Sudan to ensure a smooth transition to independence. Additionally, he mentions the possibility of examining Sudan's designation as a State Sponsor of Terrorism and assures those seeking a future of dignity and peace that they will have a steady partner in the United States.